President Obama had a phone call with the Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi, Sheikh Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan. They discussed the situation in Syria and the need to fight against ISIL and al-Qa'ida. They also talked about stabilizing areas in Iraq that have been liberated from ISIL. The President expressed concern about the renewed fighting in Yemen and the need for an immediate ceasefire and political settlement. He also thanked the United Arab Emirates for their commitment to addressing the global refugee crisis. They agreed on the importance of addressing climate change and supporting measures to reduce carbon emissions from aviation. Both leaders expressed their determination to strengthen bilateral cooperation.